Vexor is an ORIGINAL reimplementation written from scratch in Zig. Its runtime
behavior is byte-for-byte compatible with the Agave validator by design. That
compatibility was achieved by using the Apache-2.0 licensed projects below as
REFERENCE IMPLEMENTATIONS and DIFFERENTIAL TEST ORACLES — reading their source,
reimplementing the behavior in Zig, and verifying bit-for-bit against their
output. Vexor links NONE of their code at runtime (the crypto is a pure-Zig
reimplementation; see PROVENANCE.md).

  • Agave — Anza  (anza-xyz/agave), Apache-2.0.
      Primary behavioral reference: consensus / fork choice, SVM + sBPF
      execution, compute-budget & cost model, CPI, vote / stake / loader
      programs, sysvars, account (LtHash) hashing.

  • Firedancer — Jump Crypto  (firedancer-io/firedancer), Apache-2.0.
      Reference for leaf cryptography (the "Ballet" ed25519 / blake3 / bn254 /
      poseidon routines) and select high-performance data structures.
      NOTE: Vexor no longer links Firedancer at all — its cryptography is an
      independent pure-Zig reimplementation, unconditionally (the historical
      -Dpure_zig build flag is retained as a no-op for recipe compatibility).

  • Sig — Syndica  (Syndica/sig), Apache-2.0.
      Reference for Zig-idiomatic Solana structures during early bring-up.
      NOTE: the one subsystem that carried Sig-derived code — the vote-program
      transplant used as a differential oracle while Vexor's own vote executor
      was validated — has been removed. Vexor's vote program, like the rest of
      the client, is now an independent reimplementation; Vexor's
      implementations are independent of Sig at both build and runtime.

Per-subsystem provenance — exactly which Vexor file/function reimplements which
upstream source, and whether it was reimplemented, ported, or verified
byte-exact — is maintained in PROVENANCE.md (the provenance ledger).

Vexor also vendors one piece of third-party code directly (not a behavioral
reference — actual linked source):

  • blst — Supranational LLC  (supranational/blst), Apache-2.0.
      BLS12-381 pairing-cryptography library, vendored at vendor/blst/ and
      built directly from its C/assembly source. See vendor/blst/LICENSE for
      the license text as distributed by Supranational.

